WEBVTT

01:26.580 --> 01:34.950
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.340 --> 01:37.940
[Episode 10]

01:52.110 --> 01:55.350
[Snack Shop]

02:01.070 --> 02:04.450
[Snack Shop]

02:01.650 --> 02:02.310
Xu Shengli.

02:18.210 --> 02:20.690
His parents and my mom are old friends.

02:22.030 --> 02:22.930
I was able to come to Beijing

02:22.930 --> 02:24.460
and take classes with Mr. Zheng

02:24.460 --> 02:26.390
thanks to Kang Shunyin's parents.

02:28.300 --> 02:29.900
We're very grateful to them.

02:30.930 --> 02:32.730
Not long after classes started,

02:33.090 --> 02:34.150
Kang Shunyin's mother

02:34.150 --> 02:35.470
suddenly said she wanted to set

02:35.470 --> 02:36.800
Kang Shunyin up with me.

02:37.410 --> 02:38.610
We met a few times.

02:39.060 --> 02:40.610
But I realized that he was

02:40.860 --> 02:42.460
very emotionally unstable.

02:42.800 --> 02:43.630
And in his daily life,

02:43.630 --> 02:45.490
he seemed like a total mama's boy.

02:46.130 --> 02:48.130
We were definitely not a good match.

02:50.710 --> 02:51.579
So my mom and I

02:51.590 --> 02:53.650
set things straight with his family.

02:54.930 --> 02:56.450
But after a while,

02:56.930 --> 02:58.370
rumors started spreading in town

02:58.370 --> 03:00.900
that Kang Shunyin and I
were getting engaged.

03:01.370 --> 03:02.810
His family spread them.

03:04.590 --> 03:06.180
Before we could even argue with them,

03:06.180 --> 03:08.500
they sent gold and silver jewelry,

03:08.970 --> 03:09.930
and all sorts of stuff

03:09.930 --> 03:10.940
to my house.

03:11.150 --> 03:12.610
We refused them on the spot

03:12.740 --> 03:14.240
and returned everything.

03:15.470 --> 03:17.400
But they wouldn't listen to a word.

03:18.780 --> 03:20.470
Then they started making trouble
for no reason.

03:20.470 --> 03:22.250
That's just shameless!

03:22.750 --> 03:23.970
You made it clear

03:23.970 --> 03:24.970
and rejected him.

03:25.590 --> 03:27.910
How dare he still
come to Beijing to find you?

03:27.910 --> 03:28.670
He's sick.

03:34.180 --> 03:35.420
Actually, I'm okay.

03:36.430 --> 03:37.690
It's mainly my family.

03:39.120 --> 03:40.450
They're in a tough spot.

03:42.190 --> 03:43.850
I feel really guilty about it.

03:45.470 --> 03:46.290
True.

03:47.360 --> 03:48.530
In small towns like that,

03:48.530 --> 03:50.390
everyone knows everyone.

03:50.970 --> 03:53.700
Families have known each other
for generations.

03:53.900 --> 03:55.500
You bump into them everywhere.

03:55.500 --> 03:57.950
It must be awkward for your parents.

04:08.300 --> 04:09.230
Have you been...

04:10.150 --> 04:11.350
following me lately?

04:12.590 --> 04:14.650
I... I was just worried

04:14.680 --> 04:16.120
he might come find you again

04:16.120 --> 04:17.480
and do something crazy.

04:20.269 --> 04:20.890
Thank you.

04:22.870 --> 04:25.070
And thanks for changing the lock for us.

04:26.420 --> 04:27.990
No problem. No big deal.

04:28.420 --> 04:29.080
No big deal.

04:31.210 --> 04:31.890
Isn't the film crew

04:31.890 --> 04:33.030
pretty busy lately?

04:33.560 --> 04:34.630
You don't need to worry.

04:34.630 --> 04:35.690
If anything really happens,

04:35.690 --> 04:36.890
I'll call the police.

04:38.250 --> 04:39.460
Wait a second.

04:55.100 --> 04:56.450
This is pepper spray.

04:57.040 --> 04:58.170
It's really strong.

04:58.270 --> 04:59.050
I tried it.

04:59.390 --> 05:00.920
It sprays really far. Look.

05:01.620 --> 05:02.180
This far.

05:02.750 --> 05:03.120
Here.

05:03.540 --> 05:04.680
If you meet a bad guy in the future,

05:04.680 --> 05:05.300
aim at him,

05:05.310 --> 05:06.250
and just... just spray.

05:06.250 --> 05:06.910
Just spray.

05:06.930 --> 05:08.370
He definitely won't be able to handle it.

05:08.370 --> 05:09.000
Try it.

05:14.370 --> 05:16.070
I... I'm not a bad guy.

05:22.690 --> 05:23.390
Now that I have

05:23.390 --> 05:24.720
such a powerful weapon,

05:25.130 --> 05:26.790
I won't be afraid of anything.

05:35.330 --> 05:36.890
Are you going to the set today?

05:36.890 --> 05:37.300
Yes.

05:37.860 --> 05:38.620
Ranran said she's also going to

05:38.620 --> 05:39.740
audition for your film crew.

05:39.740 --> 05:41.200
Audition for my film crew?

05:41.300 --> 05:42.700
Zongbao introduced her.

05:42.980 --> 05:43.640
Zongbao...

05:47.420 --> 05:48.940
That Guo Zongbao, he...

05:51.300 --> 05:52.620
He's abusing his power!

05:52.620 --> 05:54.300
Father, let me explain.

05:54.450 --> 05:55.600
It's not like that.

05:55.800 --> 05:56.650
Ruping,

05:56.950 --> 05:58.650
you'll be the death of me!

05:59.480 --> 06:02.390
I brought you back to this manor,

06:02.570 --> 06:03.730
but I never expected

06:04.180 --> 06:05.620
that you would turn my home

06:05.620 --> 06:08.130
upside down!

06:15.190 --> 06:15.750
Father,

06:16.510 --> 06:18.730
I have a humble status in this family.

06:19.130 --> 06:21.070
How would I dare to be unruly?

06:22.180 --> 06:22.660
Cut.

06:25.690 --> 06:26.920
Not bad.

06:27.620 --> 06:28.820
I noticed something.

06:28.890 --> 06:29.810
Just now,

06:29.860 --> 06:31.010
your expression

06:31.010 --> 06:32.010
when you knelt down

06:32.010 --> 06:33.870
and the expression when you looked up

06:33.870 --> 06:34.800
were different.

06:35.390 --> 06:36.970
Is this your own design?

06:37.330 --> 06:37.930
Director,

06:38.100 --> 06:39.840
when I was reading this scene,

06:39.950 --> 06:41.570
I could feel that this character

06:41.570 --> 06:43.030
might not be as direct

06:43.060 --> 06:44.100
or as silly

06:44.159 --> 06:44.820
as she acts.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.750
Although it's just
a section of the script,

06:46.750 --> 06:48.080
I can feel that

06:48.190 --> 06:49.740
this is a way to protect herself

06:49.740 --> 06:50.560
as an illegitimate daughter

06:50.560 --> 06:52.010
in the household.

06:52.770 --> 06:53.750
Maybe because I'm also all alone

06:53.750 --> 06:54.680
out here,

06:54.800 --> 06:55.720
I can really relate to

06:55.720 --> 06:56.680
how she feels.

06:57.300 --> 06:57.790
Good.

06:57.890 --> 06:58.490
Of course,

06:58.810 --> 07:00.000
this scene is written

07:00.000 --> 07:01.300
with such depth.

07:01.420 --> 07:02.810
I can totally feel

07:02.860 --> 07:04.630
the screenwriter's dedication.

07:04.630 --> 07:06.570
The screenwriter
not only understood the character,

07:06.570 --> 07:08.030
but also made such a small role

07:08.030 --> 07:09.310
so well-rounded.

07:09.600 --> 07:10.920
It's really amazing.

07:11.240 --> 07:12.100
Amazing.

07:15.300 --> 07:16.770
The Master was played well too.

07:16.770 --> 07:17.970
Thank you, Director.

07:18.360 --> 07:19.160
It's just that

07:19.450 --> 07:20.550
the accent

07:21.630 --> 07:23.570
might not be suitable for the Master.

07:23.570 --> 07:24.250
So why not let him

07:24.250 --> 07:25.270
play the butler?

07:25.330 --> 07:26.180
Sure!

07:26.190 --> 07:27.460
Director, sure.

07:27.570 --> 07:28.430
A butler works too.

07:28.430 --> 07:29.390
Good.

07:29.600 --> 07:29.950
I...

07:30.000 --> 07:31.400
Go back and wait for news.

07:31.430 --> 07:32.680
-Thank you, sirs.
-Thank you, Director.

07:32.680 --> 07:33.190
Thank you, everyone.

07:33.190 --> 07:33.480
Thank you.

07:33.480 --> 07:34.430
Next group, get ready.

07:34.430 --> 07:35.390
Okay.

07:36.500 --> 07:38.360
This scene is written quite well.

07:39.010 --> 07:39.470
Indeed.

07:40.110 --> 07:41.230
Whose idea was it?

07:41.560 --> 07:42.760
It was all Xu's idea.

07:45.190 --> 07:45.520
Good.

07:46.310 --> 07:46.690
Good.

07:48.830 --> 07:49.500
Next group.

07:49.690 --> 07:50.750
Are you ready?

07:51.040 --> 07:52.040
Ready, Director.

07:55.010 --> 07:56.340
Great Screenwriter Xu,

07:56.500 --> 07:57.830
have some pig trotters.

07:58.390 --> 08:00.080
We've all studied

08:00.250 --> 08:02.260
the script you wrote.

08:03.160 --> 08:04.770
It's written so well.

08:05.330 --> 08:07.580
If I could really act in it,

08:07.870 --> 08:09.770
could you give me some pointers?

08:09.860 --> 08:11.320
I can't give you pointers.

08:12.040 --> 08:14.000
You're treating me like a stranger, too.

08:14.000 --> 08:14.720
You think I won't help you

08:14.720 --> 08:15.580
if you just ask?

08:16.300 --> 08:17.480
What is this?

08:17.770 --> 08:18.530
The crew

08:18.800 --> 08:20.200
has rules.

08:20.500 --> 08:22.080
I can't get you in trouble.

08:22.360 --> 08:23.680
If I really asked you for it,

08:23.680 --> 08:24.940
would you give it to me?

08:25.100 --> 08:25.500
Right?

08:26.780 --> 08:28.640
Have some trotters. Don't be shy.

08:30.120 --> 08:31.050
Eat it yourself.

08:31.270 --> 08:32.309
It's hot.

08:36.120 --> 08:36.909
Shen!

08:39.549 --> 08:40.150
Mr. Xu.

08:43.700 --> 08:45.030
I also want to thank you.

08:47.950 --> 08:49.360
Thanking me empty-handed?

08:49.360 --> 08:49.690
Here.

08:50.320 --> 08:51.710
It's hot!

08:54.100 --> 08:55.960
Big pig trotters stewed by Mr. Guo.

08:55.960 --> 08:57.100
I contributed.

08:57.340 --> 08:58.820
A little token of appreciation
from both of us

08:58.820 --> 09:00.740
for the future great screenwriter.

09:00.740 --> 09:01.580
Great screenwriter.

09:01.580 --> 09:02.550
What are we eating today?

09:02.550 --> 09:04.050
Why does it smell so good?

09:05.600 --> 09:06.510
Pig trotters!

09:07.670 --> 09:08.030
What?

09:08.030 --> 09:09.580
It's for the great screenwriter.

09:09.580 --> 09:10.360
Exactly.

09:12.030 --> 09:12.580
Hey...

09:13.130 --> 09:14.590
You're dressed so nicely.

09:15.000 --> 09:16.100
Where are you going?

09:16.100 --> 09:17.830
Who are you going on a date with?

09:18.620 --> 09:20.300
Zhuang Zhuang styled me.

09:20.790 --> 09:21.790
Does it look good?

09:22.200 --> 09:23.000
It looks good.

09:24.440 --> 09:26.440
If I audition for
the song and dance troupe,

09:26.440 --> 09:27.240
I could ask her

09:27.240 --> 09:28.270
to help style me too.

09:28.270 --> 09:29.700
You want to audition
for the song and dance troupe?

09:29.700 --> 09:31.190
Come on.

09:31.700 --> 09:32.770
Have some trotters.

09:32.770 --> 09:34.100
One per person. Come on.

09:34.770 --> 09:35.750
Our lives

09:35.840 --> 09:37.080
are getting better and better.

09:37.080 --> 09:38.050
-It’s for the scriptwriter.
-From now on,

09:38.050 --> 09:39.860
we'll eat trotters every day, okay?

09:39.860 --> 09:40.190
Here.

09:41.040 --> 09:41.900
Have some more.

09:43.600 --> 09:44.740
Here's the audition plan I just wrote.

09:44.740 --> 09:45.210
Take a look.

09:45.210 --> 09:45.600
Okay.

09:45.840 --> 09:46.590
Let me see.

09:46.890 --> 09:48.430
-Is it good?
-It’s so delicious.

09:48.430 --> 09:50.460
Look how excited Xuan is.

09:50.920 --> 09:51.680
Decline.

09:52.100 --> 09:53.930
Poetry is eternal.

09:54.270 --> 09:55.870
Now, all over the streets...

09:56.870 --> 09:59.000
It can make the living die,

09:59.740 --> 10:01.460
and the dead come back to life.

10:02.050 --> 10:02.790
This hatred,

10:03.170 --> 10:04.320
formless,

10:04.820 --> 10:06.120
is held in the palm

10:06.580 --> 10:07.650
like a thorn.

10:09.030 --> 10:10.790
When I no longer cling to love,

10:11.390 --> 10:13.450
when I'm no longer trapped in hate...

11:06.600 --> 11:07.200
All right.

11:07.320 --> 11:08.440
That's enough, candidate.

11:08.440 --> 11:09.160
Sir,

11:09.820 --> 11:11.750
I haven't played the best part yet.

11:12.630 --> 11:13.200
That will do.

11:13.200 --> 11:14.330
We've heard enough.

11:15.510 --> 11:16.910
Next candidate, please.

11:17.750 --> 11:18.700
Thank you, sirs.

11:20.750 --> 11:22.010
See? You made the list.

11:22.010 --> 11:23.140
Right in the middle.

11:23.370 --> 11:24.630
That's me. Did you see?

11:25.600 --> 11:26.460
How about that?

11:27.760 --> 11:28.380
[Fenghua Song and Dance Troupe Results]
[Musicians]

11:28.410 --> 11:30.060
[Backup Singers]

11:30.080 --> 11:31.240
[Backup Dancers]

11:41.390 --> 11:43.050
I told you I'd get in this time.

11:43.050 --> 11:43.910
What do you say?

11:44.240 --> 11:45.300
You're confident.

11:45.790 --> 11:46.320
Let's go.

11:55.270 --> 11:55.870
Hello, Director.

11:55.870 --> 11:57.220
My name is Tao Liangliang.

11:57.220 --> 11:58.080
I just

11:58.390 --> 11:59.150
checked the list.

11:59.150 --> 12:00.210
My name isn't on it.

12:00.220 --> 12:01.440
I wanted to ask

12:02.340 --> 12:03.470
wh-what's going on?

12:06.090 --> 12:07.010
Come on in.

12:08.860 --> 12:09.460
Thank you.

12:11.700 --> 12:12.630
Well...

12:13.100 --> 12:14.100
Here's the thing.

12:14.220 --> 12:15.510
Since the list is already posted,

12:15.510 --> 12:16.640
and you're not on it,

12:16.910 --> 12:18.910
you can try again next year.

12:19.200 --> 12:21.400
But I've auditioned twice already.

12:21.720 --> 12:22.360
I've even come here

12:22.360 --> 12:23.560
several times.

12:23.840 --> 12:25.660
-Twice isn't a lot.
-I just want…

12:25.940 --> 12:26.890
Some people

12:26.960 --> 12:29.560
try seven or eight times
and still don't get in.

12:30.840 --> 12:32.290
Director, since I'm here today,

12:32.290 --> 12:34.090
can I play a piece just for you...

12:35.790 --> 12:37.330
in your office?

12:37.370 --> 12:37.910
Now, now.

12:37.940 --> 12:38.870
No need, no need.

12:39.600 --> 12:40.330
Take it easy.

12:40.530 --> 12:41.260
Take it easy.

12:42.750 --> 12:43.320
Here.

12:43.600 --> 12:44.460
Come, sit down.

12:47.440 --> 12:48.300
Young man,

12:48.750 --> 12:50.410
you've already auditioned for our troupe,

12:50.410 --> 12:51.050
so we've definitely heard

12:51.050 --> 12:52.110
your performance.

12:54.050 --> 12:55.310
Here's the situation.

12:55.410 --> 12:56.610
This year, our troupe

12:56.940 --> 12:58.150
has a very limited quota

12:58.150 --> 12:59.390
for saxophone players.

12:59.390 --> 13:00.510
We need

13:00.510 --> 13:02.220
extremely professional people.

13:02.220 --> 13:04.000
I'm very professional.

13:04.390 --> 13:05.270
Director, look.

13:05.270 --> 13:06.460
I've been dreaming day and night

13:06.460 --> 13:07.410
about joining this troupe.

13:07.410 --> 13:09.010
If I can get in,

13:09.170 --> 13:10.550
I'll put my heart and soul

13:10.550 --> 13:12.120
into performing for everyone.

13:12.120 --> 13:13.010
If you tell me to climb a mountain,

13:13.010 --> 13:14.580
I won't just lie in the grass.

13:14.580 --> 13:15.550
Whatever you tell me to do,

13:15.550 --> 13:16.480
I'll do it.

13:16.670 --> 13:17.410
And I'm not afraid

13:17.410 --> 13:19.010
of hardship or fatigue.

13:19.080 --> 13:20.240
-I…
-Okay, okay.

13:20.440 --> 13:21.190
This kid...

13:22.910 --> 13:23.770
How about this?

13:24.770 --> 13:25.630
Let me ask you,

13:26.100 --> 13:27.480
who is

13:27.480 --> 13:28.480
your sax teacher?

13:32.130 --> 13:34.390
I had a teacher when I was young,

13:34.910 --> 13:36.050
but later I...

13:36.070 --> 13:36.870
Self-taught?

13:37.440 --> 13:37.860
Yes.

13:39.390 --> 13:40.390
Here's the thing.

13:40.860 --> 13:42.710
I have a suggestion for you.

13:43.440 --> 13:44.400
Find a teacher

13:45.270 --> 13:46.130
and seriously,

13:46.290 --> 13:48.890
systematically,
start with the basics again.

13:54.860 --> 13:56.920
Lamb skewers! Get your lamb skewers!

14:12.100 --> 14:13.430
What are you doing here?

14:13.620 --> 14:15.820
You knew it was me without even looking?

14:20.670 --> 14:21.080
Sit.

14:28.320 --> 14:29.670
Every day when I wake up,

14:31.770 --> 14:33.960
I look at that tiny half-window.

14:34.620 --> 14:36.280
With people coming and going,

14:37.050 --> 14:38.490
all I can see

14:39.770 --> 14:41.240
are their shoes.

14:47.080 --> 14:49.250
I live like a mole every day.

14:51.120 --> 14:52.250
I was able to hold on

14:54.630 --> 14:56.830
only because of that little bit of hope.

15:06.120 --> 15:07.310
I heard about it.

15:08.340 --> 15:09.440
I saw you weren't in your room

15:09.440 --> 15:11.570
and I couldn't find you anywhere else,

15:12.780 --> 15:14.040
so I came here to check.

15:17.600 --> 15:19.130
Why were you looking for me?

15:19.770 --> 15:21.320
To... To laugh at you.

15:21.340 --> 15:22.230
Laugh at me?

15:26.170 --> 15:27.560
I've got thick skin.

15:32.670 --> 15:33.460
Liangliang,

15:35.530 --> 15:36.990
you seriously play the sax

15:37.040 --> 15:38.950
really well.

15:39.130 --> 15:41.190
It's not that you're not good enough.

15:41.440 --> 15:43.040
It's that they have no taste.

15:43.600 --> 15:44.190
Really.

15:44.510 --> 15:47.040
They just don't know quality
when they see it.

15:55.530 --> 15:56.870
As long as you do.

16:00.630 --> 16:01.690
Let's have a drink.

16:03.930 --> 16:05.430
There's a new bottle here.

16:09.240 --> 16:09.700
Here.

16:16.850 --> 16:18.820
Dad, Dad. Here.
Give it to me. Let me do it.

16:18.820 --> 16:19.870
Let me do it for you.

16:19.870 --> 16:20.480
No, no, no.

16:20.480 --> 16:23.320
No need.
Those hands are for playing the saxophone.

16:23.320 --> 16:24.620
I rarely get to come back.

16:24.620 --> 16:25.270
Let me help you.

16:25.270 --> 16:26.530
Look at this. How is it?

16:27.620 --> 16:29.110
My skills have improved, right?

16:29.110 --> 16:30.670
Look at how I flip these.

16:30.700 --> 16:32.270
Here, Mom, Dad.

16:32.370 --> 16:34.170
Let me pour for both of you.

16:40.700 --> 16:41.310
Okay.

16:43.150 --> 16:44.070
Why do I have

16:44.100 --> 16:45.500
a bad feeling about this?

16:47.030 --> 16:48.970
Dad, you're too paranoid.

16:49.030 --> 16:51.090
I've learned my lessons the hard way.

16:51.270 --> 16:52.800
Raising you all these years

16:52.940 --> 16:55.070
has taught me more than the real world.

16:56.500 --> 16:57.040
Dad,

16:57.370 --> 16:59.300
well, you're the one who taught me.

16:59.390 --> 17:00.820
I taught you how to cook,

17:01.010 --> 17:02.980
but I didn't teach you
how to play that thing.

17:02.980 --> 17:04.839
You picked that up all on your own.

17:05.500 --> 17:06.960
Alright. Hurry up and eat.

17:07.050 --> 17:08.380
Let's talk while we eat.

17:08.680 --> 17:09.300
Mom, Dad,

17:10.089 --> 17:11.280
for over 20 years,

17:11.880 --> 17:13.630
I've made you two worry a lot.

17:14.500 --> 17:16.150
As a son,

17:17.790 --> 17:18.609
I'm not the same

17:18.609 --> 17:19.940
as other people's sons.

17:20.310 --> 17:21.710
I haven't made you proud.

17:22.010 --> 17:23.260
But I swear,

17:24.160 --> 17:25.000
in the future,

17:25.290 --> 17:26.640
if I make something of myself

17:26.640 --> 17:28.180
and make it big,

17:28.880 --> 17:29.770
I promise

17:30.070 --> 17:31.670
I'll treat you like royalty.

17:32.110 --> 17:32.770
Bottoms up!

17:34.200 --> 17:34.770
You...

17:35.460 --> 17:36.960
Doing this all of a sudden,

17:36.960 --> 17:37.920
it's not just your dad who's confused.

17:37.920 --> 17:38.940
Even I feel

17:38.940 --> 17:40.470
a bit uneasy.

17:40.550 --> 17:42.290
See? What did I tell you?

17:44.330 --> 17:45.510
Recently,

17:46.590 --> 17:48.320
I've figured some things out.

17:48.400 --> 17:51.400
I've been thinking it over,
and it doesn't feel right.

17:51.530 --> 17:52.380
So,

17:54.460 --> 17:55.310
I won't carry

17:56.420 --> 17:57.550
this sax around

17:57.550 --> 17:58.480
to busk anymore.

18:00.330 --> 18:01.570
I'll work hard

18:02.250 --> 18:03.580
and turn over a new leaf!

18:04.920 --> 18:06.390
Pinch me.

18:06.500 --> 18:08.120
I feel like I'm dreaming.

18:09.070 --> 18:09.880
He's grown up.

18:10.310 --> 18:11.370
He's sensible now.

18:11.480 --> 18:12.220
Have some food.

18:12.220 --> 18:13.800
Taste your son's cooking.

18:14.510 --> 18:16.080
Come on, try it.

18:19.850 --> 18:21.310
You're really something,

18:22.460 --> 18:23.110
Son,

18:23.160 --> 18:24.620
what do you plan to do next?

18:24.790 --> 18:26.310
Tell us as soon as you've decided.

18:26.310 --> 18:26.720
I...

18:26.770 --> 18:27.700
No need to say it.

18:27.980 --> 18:29.240
I've already guessed.

18:30.050 --> 18:30.830
As soon as he came in,

18:30.830 --> 18:32.050
he took over my ladle,

18:32.500 --> 18:34.090
wanting to show me his skills.

18:34.090 --> 18:35.430
You've been mad at me all these years,

18:35.430 --> 18:36.830
renting a place outside.

18:37.010 --> 18:38.750
But lately, I keep seeing you.

18:39.000 --> 18:39.900
Quite a few times now.

18:39.900 --> 18:40.530
You've been hanging around

18:40.530 --> 18:42.250
the entrance of our restaurant.

18:42.250 --> 18:44.290
You bolt the moment I see you.

18:44.440 --> 18:45.160
Why?

18:45.350 --> 18:46.420
Is that even a question?

18:46.420 --> 18:47.960
You used to be so harsh.

18:47.960 --> 18:49.100
He's afraid of you.

18:49.250 --> 18:51.920
If you want to learn the trade,
just say so.

18:52.030 --> 18:53.430
Nothing to be shy about.

18:53.790 --> 18:55.790
A returned prodigal
is worth more than gold.

18:55.790 --> 18:56.330
Today,

18:56.700 --> 18:58.510
I'll pass down our family's

18:58.510 --> 18:59.420
secret fried sauce recipe

18:59.420 --> 19:00.110
to you.

19:03.770 --> 19:04.240
Dad.

19:05.460 --> 19:07.360
Sometimes, I think

19:07.550 --> 19:09.180
playing the sax

19:09.500 --> 19:11.110
doesn't have much of a future.

19:11.110 --> 19:11.760
Yeah.

19:11.790 --> 19:13.920
That thing won't put food on the table.

19:14.180 --> 19:15.530
You should've gotten rid of it long ago.

19:15.530 --> 19:17.660
Sometimes it can put food on the table.

19:17.680 --> 19:19.480
Maybe it can feed me even better.

19:19.500 --> 19:20.640
Look at this fried sauce.

19:20.640 --> 19:21.420
It has a mix of fatty and lean meat.

19:21.420 --> 19:22.920
Put the fatty meat in first.

19:22.920 --> 19:24.220
Render it into cracklings.

19:24.220 --> 19:25.310
Then add the lean meat.

19:25.310 --> 19:25.680
No,

19:25.680 --> 19:27.140
use less of this fat.

19:27.140 --> 19:27.720
It's...

19:27.980 --> 19:28.750
too much.

19:29.090 --> 19:30.850
Then add some lean meat.

19:33.700 --> 19:35.030
Dad, I'll be straight with you.

19:35.030 --> 19:37.830
I want to audition
for a song and dance troupe here.

19:38.350 --> 19:40.400
The teachers there

19:40.500 --> 19:41.680
think your son

19:42.330 --> 19:44.660
is a rising star

19:44.660 --> 19:46.580
with a bright future.

19:52.440 --> 19:53.930
Their troupe

19:54.610 --> 19:56.750
needs a sax player.

19:56.800 --> 19:58.710
I happen to play the sax.

19:59.550 --> 20:01.010
I have to help them

20:01.010 --> 20:02.200
return to their former glory.

20:02.200 --> 20:02.850
I need to step it up,

20:02.850 --> 20:03.870
so I need to hire

20:03.900 --> 20:04.480
an instructor

20:04.480 --> 20:05.880
to give me some pointers.

20:09.940 --> 20:10.720
I'll be frank.

20:10.720 --> 20:11.850
I need to pay

20:11.850 --> 20:13.290
in order to hire a sax teacher.

20:13.290 --> 20:14.740
I want to get some money

20:14.830 --> 20:15.890
from you and my mom.

20:15.940 --> 20:16.940
I'll pay you back.

20:22.160 --> 20:22.720
Dad,

20:22.920 --> 20:24.030
don't worry.

20:24.460 --> 20:25.700
I definitely won't let this money

20:25.700 --> 20:27.110
go down the drain.

20:27.220 --> 20:28.530
"Return what you borrow,
and it's easy to borrow again."

20:28.530 --> 20:29.070
Deal?

20:29.160 --> 20:30.160
Think about it.

20:30.160 --> 20:31.940
Let me toss the wok for you. Come on.

20:31.940 --> 20:32.640
Move.

20:32.640 --> 20:33.760
You do it? Let me.

20:33.850 --> 20:34.310
This...

20:35.680 --> 20:36.030
I...

20:44.150 --> 20:45.750
What's wrong? What's wrong?

20:47.270 --> 20:48.370
What happened?

20:49.300 --> 20:49.740
Brag.

20:50.550 --> 20:51.540
Brag harder!

20:52.160 --> 20:52.460
Dad.

20:53.070 --> 20:54.250
I wasn't bragging.

20:54.270 --> 20:55.330
Go play in the shop.

20:56.140 --> 20:56.900
Hold that

20:56.900 --> 20:58.090
solid silver chamber pot of yours

20:58.090 --> 20:59.090
and go play in my shop.

20:59.090 --> 21:00.290
How could I?

21:00.290 --> 21:01.510
Listen to what he's saying.

21:01.510 --> 21:02.570
You need tuition?

21:02.850 --> 21:03.850
Earn it yourself!

21:03.870 --> 21:04.880
I'm hiring you.

21:05.610 --> 21:07.090
What exactly is going on?

21:07.140 --> 21:08.890
My son is scheming against me!

21:09.400 --> 21:09.980
No—

21:12.240 --> 21:12.840
Your foot.

21:13.570 --> 21:14.900
-What happened to your foot?
-Dad.

21:14.900 --> 21:16.300
You're really paying me?

21:17.220 --> 21:19.680
I'm really going to
the shop tomorrow, then.

21:34.440 --> 21:36.420
Does this work?

21:41.550 --> 21:43.440
This painting today...

21:44.110 --> 21:45.510
looks a bit interesting.

21:46.790 --> 21:48.030
What do you mean by "interesting"?

21:48.030 --> 21:49.240
Interesting in what way?

21:49.240 --> 21:51.500
What does "a bit interesting" even mean?

21:52.460 --> 21:54.270
It means...

21:54.330 --> 21:55.690
in this hot weather,

21:55.810 --> 21:57.070
under the blazing sun,

21:57.960 --> 22:00.160
seeing the hard work you put in, it's...

22:00.180 --> 22:01.180
not bad.

22:01.200 --> 22:01.930
Pretty good.

22:02.770 --> 22:03.850
From what you're saying,

22:03.850 --> 22:05.450
you think my painting is bad.

22:07.660 --> 22:08.770
Everyone is different.

22:08.770 --> 22:09.350
It's subjective.

22:09.350 --> 22:10.940
There's no good or bad.

22:11.140 --> 22:13.880
It's just about
whether you like it or not.

22:13.980 --> 22:14.940
You watch me every day.

22:14.940 --> 22:16.110
Will things change
because you're watching?

22:16.110 --> 22:17.480
What you're doing

22:17.550 --> 22:18.330
is even more annoying

22:18.330 --> 22:19.660
than those bossy old men

22:19.680 --> 22:21.540
watching people watching chess.

22:21.680 --> 22:23.140
Oh, you...

22:25.030 --> 22:26.230
Let me put it this way.

22:27.270 --> 22:30.000
Let's be open and honest,

22:30.000 --> 22:31.060
and tell the truth.

22:34.570 --> 22:36.330
We are in the same field.

22:37.880 --> 22:39.740
I'm also a painter.

22:42.660 --> 22:43.790
Don't use your hobby

22:43.810 --> 22:45.110
to compete with my passion.

22:45.110 --> 22:45.900
The peonies you learned to paint

22:45.900 --> 22:48.160
at the senior university doesn't count.

22:48.460 --> 22:49.590
I want to

22:50.380 --> 22:51.640
collaborate with you.

23:14.070 --> 23:15.390
What are you doing?

23:16.010 --> 23:17.470
You're playing way too loud.

23:17.470 --> 23:19.130
How is anyone supposed to eat?

23:19.140 --> 23:19.940
Get your boss.

23:21.440 --> 23:22.170
He's inside.

23:26.890 --> 23:27.850
Who's the boss?

23:29.250 --> 23:29.750
What's wrong?

23:29.750 --> 23:31.410
Is the food not to your liking?

23:31.570 --> 23:32.960
It's not about the food.

23:33.660 --> 23:34.990
It's that kid you hired.

23:35.050 --> 23:36.130
Playing that...

23:36.440 --> 23:37.350
that big horn.

23:37.660 --> 23:38.980
It scared me!

23:39.030 --> 23:40.240
That's not a horn.

23:40.330 --> 23:41.430
It's a sax.

23:41.850 --> 23:42.920
We just wanted to provide

23:42.920 --> 23:44.700
some entertainment for everyone.

23:44.700 --> 23:46.400
I'm just having a bowl of noodles.

23:46.400 --> 23:47.440
What entertainment do I need?

23:47.440 --> 23:47.840
You...

23:48.110 --> 23:49.480
If you were serving a royal banquet,

23:49.480 --> 23:50.320
maybe then.

23:51.200 --> 23:52.000
No, actually,

23:52.630 --> 23:54.140
even if I were eating a royal banquet,

23:54.140 --> 23:55.610
I still wouldn't listen to that junk.

23:55.610 --> 23:57.010
Tell him to stop right now.

23:57.010 --> 23:57.540
Alright.

23:57.940 --> 24:00.140
This plate of fried pork is on the house.

24:01.220 --> 24:02.620
Well, thanks. Thank you.

24:05.510 --> 24:06.050
Boss,

24:06.640 --> 24:08.240
why do you even bother?

24:08.640 --> 24:09.270
That kid

24:10.140 --> 24:11.690
looks like a hooligan.

24:11.900 --> 24:13.200
He doesn't look like he comes from

24:13.200 --> 24:14.330
a decent family.

24:15.220 --> 24:15.880
Why on earth

24:16.070 --> 24:17.240
would you hire him?

24:18.420 --> 24:19.420
Stop right there.

24:23.590 --> 24:24.670
What's this for?

24:24.880 --> 24:26.550
This food isn't suitable for you.

24:26.550 --> 24:28.480
I won't charge you for the noodles.

24:50.500 --> 24:52.840
This is my workshop.

24:53.940 --> 24:55.010
These young people

24:55.090 --> 24:56.500
are just like you.

24:56.900 --> 24:58.920
They come from all over the country.

24:59.550 --> 25:01.700
They used to be like you,

25:01.850 --> 25:02.930
roaming about.

25:04.660 --> 25:07.010
They couldn't make a living anymore,

25:07.030 --> 25:08.320
unable to afford food.

25:08.960 --> 25:09.880
It's tough.

25:10.700 --> 25:12.970
They call themselves artists

25:13.330 --> 25:14.680
but wear ragged underwear.

25:14.680 --> 25:15.460
Talk about art

25:15.460 --> 25:16.620
and they yap on and on

25:16.660 --> 25:18.000
through the night without stopping.

25:18.000 --> 25:19.540
Talk to them about life

25:20.440 --> 25:21.500
and they go silent.

25:23.610 --> 25:25.940
I felt sorry for them,

25:26.090 --> 25:28.300
so I gathered them here.

25:30.320 --> 25:31.720
Room and board included.

25:31.830 --> 25:32.560
How about it?

25:32.810 --> 25:34.220
Do you want to join

25:34.290 --> 25:35.490
our big family?

25:38.050 --> 25:38.640
Art

25:39.610 --> 25:40.640
is ruined by people

25:40.640 --> 25:41.320
like you.

25:42.810 --> 25:43.570
Young man.

25:44.240 --> 25:46.100
The sea of bitterness is endless.

25:46.140 --> 25:46.850
You can't talk art

25:46.850 --> 25:48.500
on an empty stomach.

25:48.550 --> 25:50.960
You can only talk art when you're full.

25:51.610 --> 25:53.270
Think about it.

25:54.660 --> 25:55.140
Old man.

25:56.520 --> 25:58.160
"Man does not live by bread alone."

25:58.160 --> 25:58.620
Well...

25:58.680 --> 25:59.960
But judging by your air,

25:59.960 --> 26:00.790
I bet you don't even know

26:00.790 --> 26:01.920
who Dostoyevsky is.

26:01.960 --> 26:02.940
What?

26:03.000 --> 26:03.860
Let me tell you.

26:03.920 --> 26:04.740
If I, Cao Ye,

26:05.070 --> 26:06.000
one day

26:06.010 --> 26:07.240
sink so low as to have to come here

26:07.240 --> 26:08.150
to paint fakes,

26:08.680 --> 26:10.480
I'd rather go back home and farm.

26:12.010 --> 26:13.740
Here, have some pickles.

26:14.550 --> 26:15.010
Zhuang.

26:15.140 --> 26:17.110
How's your prep
for the troupe audition going?

26:17.110 --> 26:18.040
It's going okay.

26:19.700 --> 26:20.320
By the way,

26:21.090 --> 26:22.940
when you're acting on set,

26:23.090 --> 26:24.890
are there a lot of people around?

26:25.110 --> 26:26.330
Tons.

26:26.460 --> 26:27.520
Do you get nervous?

26:28.960 --> 26:29.470
I do.

26:32.610 --> 26:32.980
Here.

26:34.330 --> 26:34.920
The other day

26:34.920 --> 26:36.130
in class,

26:36.550 --> 26:37.610
the teacher brought some students

26:37.610 --> 26:38.370
to observe.

26:38.390 --> 26:39.810
With so many people, and pros at that,

26:39.810 --> 26:41.010
I got really nervous.

26:41.200 --> 26:42.390
Back when I was

26:42.550 --> 26:43.880
practicing acting,

26:44.940 --> 26:46.380
I wouldn't go anywhere quiet.

26:46.380 --> 26:47.380
I begged people every day

26:47.380 --> 26:48.510
to take me to events,

26:48.550 --> 26:49.530
just to get over

26:49.530 --> 26:50.510
my stage fright.

26:51.310 --> 26:52.400
You have no idea.

26:52.400 --> 26:53.810
Some auditions are packed

26:53.810 --> 26:55.210
with people.

26:55.460 --> 26:56.700
If you don't prepare,

26:56.720 --> 26:58.780
you'll definitely get tongue-tied.

26:59.050 --> 27:00.440
Why don't you give it a try?

27:00.440 --> 27:01.850
Go to some events

27:02.050 --> 27:02.880
and practice.

27:03.110 --> 27:04.140
There's only a month left.

27:04.140 --> 27:06.070
Where can I find a chance like that?

27:07.110 --> 27:07.940
Good point.

27:09.310 --> 27:10.640
You're already eating?

27:10.770 --> 27:12.440
I brought you some extra food.

27:12.770 --> 27:14.140
An actor gifted some seafood
to the director,

27:14.140 --> 27:15.400
so I brought some back.

27:16.900 --> 27:17.560
Thank you.

27:17.660 --> 27:18.320
No problem.

27:18.610 --> 27:19.330
Do you want to join us?

27:19.330 --> 27:20.440
No, no. You guys go ahead.

27:20.440 --> 27:20.930
I'm off.

27:21.140 --> 27:21.550
Mr. Xu!

27:21.980 --> 27:23.380
We're at a loss right now.

27:23.400 --> 27:24.930
Do you think there's a place

27:24.960 --> 27:25.880
for Zhuang Zhuang

27:25.880 --> 27:27.530
to participate in events

27:27.550 --> 27:28.530
for practice?

27:28.750 --> 27:30.110
Perform and practice...

27:30.110 --> 27:31.740
Aren't you taking the troupe audition?

27:31.740 --> 27:33.810
The teacher says I get nervous
in front of a big crowd.

27:33.810 --> 27:34.570
Zhuang,

27:34.790 --> 27:36.530
if only you were like Tao Liangliang,

27:36.530 --> 27:37.140
that would be great.

27:37.140 --> 27:40.670
The more people watching him play sax,
the more excited he gets.

27:40.750 --> 27:42.160
How about an international stage?

27:42.160 --> 27:43.420
International stage?

27:43.660 --> 27:44.720
Republic of China.

27:48.030 --> 27:49.350
Is this the place?

27:50.290 --> 27:51.240
This is it.

27:51.310 --> 27:53.030
Didn't he say next to the main gate

27:53.030 --> 27:54.070
by the parking shed,

27:54.070 --> 27:55.470
across from the ivy?

27:59.140 --> 27:59.780
He's here.

28:00.680 --> 28:02.610
-Xu, over here.
-Screenwriter Xu.

28:02.700 --> 28:03.900
Screenwriter Xu.

28:04.050 --> 28:05.290
I told you

28:05.290 --> 28:06.220
pretend you don't know me.

28:06.220 --> 28:07.550
Okay. We don't know you.

28:09.750 --> 28:11.250
The production has a limited budget,

28:11.250 --> 28:12.310
but they want professional

28:12.310 --> 28:13.130
singers

28:13.160 --> 28:14.060
and musicians.

28:14.180 --> 28:15.290
The executive director suggested

28:15.290 --> 28:15.980
finding someone

28:15.980 --> 28:16.940
to just lip-sync,

28:16.940 --> 28:18.330
but the director refused.

28:18.330 --> 28:19.790
He said people could tell.

28:21.310 --> 28:22.920
Let me remind you again.

28:23.070 --> 28:23.960
When you go in,

28:24.010 --> 28:25.930
don't say you know me.

28:26.030 --> 28:27.070
We don't know each other.

28:27.070 --> 28:28.850
Just say you're here to audition.

28:28.850 --> 28:30.650
The price is negotiable.

28:31.660 --> 28:32.420
The rest

28:32.530 --> 28:33.500
is up to you.

28:34.030 --> 28:35.070
If you get the part,

28:35.070 --> 28:36.930
it's a proper stage for hundreds.

28:36.980 --> 28:38.040
It'll be recorded.

28:38.200 --> 28:39.000
We'll be on TV.

28:39.790 --> 28:41.520
I'm fine with singing,

28:41.700 --> 28:42.660
but I've never acted before

28:42.660 --> 28:44.010
and I get stage fright.

28:44.090 --> 28:45.050
Don't worry. I'm here.

28:45.050 --> 28:46.000
There's not many people.

28:46.000 --> 28:47.250
With your professional skills,
you'll be fine.

28:47.250 --> 28:48.240
You just stand there.

28:48.240 --> 28:49.000
No need to act.

28:49.000 --> 28:50.460
Just stand there and sing.

28:50.640 --> 28:52.570
This is the audition place, right?

28:52.790 --> 28:53.830
Didn't he say it's here?

28:53.830 --> 28:54.630
It's right...

28:57.330 --> 28:57.880
Manager.

28:58.110 --> 28:59.570
They're here to audition.

29:00.110 --> 29:01.150
This building.

29:01.310 --> 29:02.890
Second floor, turn left.

29:02.920 --> 29:03.720
It's the acting department.

29:03.720 --> 29:05.050
Just go straight there.

29:05.090 --> 29:05.530
Go ahead.

29:05.530 --> 29:07.310
-Thank you, sir.
-You’re welcome.

29:07.310 --> 29:07.840
Go ahead.

29:08.290 --> 29:09.350
Secure the budget.

29:12.770 --> 29:13.700
Hello, Manager.

29:15.510 --> 29:16.040
Manager.

29:16.050 --> 29:16.540
Um...

29:16.680 --> 29:17.500
-Do you have...
-Go work.

29:17.500 --> 29:18.780
Go do your work.

29:19.040 --> 29:19.510
Okay.

29:19.720 --> 29:20.850
Don't waste my time.

29:26.990 --> 29:30.840
[Actor Waiting Area]

29:31.090 --> 29:31.660
Sir.

29:32.920 --> 29:34.950
Does this director shoot fast?

29:35.110 --> 29:36.420
When's lunch?

29:36.590 --> 29:37.740
We haven't even started filming

29:37.740 --> 29:38.510
and you're already thinking about lunch.

29:38.510 --> 29:39.310
Keep waiting.

29:39.720 --> 29:40.250
No, I...

29:42.180 --> 29:43.450
Food is everything.

29:44.590 --> 29:45.730
Won't let us eat?

29:48.200 --> 29:49.160
When is it?

29:49.460 --> 29:50.510
Don't know.

29:50.850 --> 29:51.750
I brought biscuits.

29:51.750 --> 29:52.200
Want some?

29:52.200 --> 29:53.050
No.

29:54.350 --> 29:55.080
Just hold on.

30:02.290 --> 30:03.680
I'm memorizing my lines.

30:03.680 --> 30:04.570
Keep it down.

30:08.570 --> 30:09.900
Making a ruckus again?

30:09.920 --> 30:10.520
Director.

30:10.920 --> 30:11.720
Let me tell you.

30:11.720 --> 30:13.100
You're all new actors.

30:13.610 --> 30:14.660
Getting into Director Weng's production

30:14.660 --> 30:15.650
is not easy.

30:15.740 --> 30:17.340
-Yes, yes.
-Okay, Director.

30:17.460 --> 30:18.660
Thank you, Director.

30:19.010 --> 30:19.830
At least you have some sense.

30:19.830 --> 30:20.220
Boss,

30:20.270 --> 30:21.290
they said they need to adjust

30:21.290 --> 30:22.270
the shooting schedule.

30:22.270 --> 30:22.790
Wait.

30:23.000 --> 30:24.070
Didn't we just adjust it?

30:24.070 --> 30:25.200
Why adjust it again?

30:25.290 --> 30:26.170
Well...

30:26.570 --> 30:27.440
Which scene?

30:27.940 --> 30:30.250
The scene with the butler
and the young lady.

30:30.250 --> 30:31.930
Are you two ready?

30:32.070 --> 30:32.520
Ready.

30:32.550 --> 30:33.710
I'm all ready.

30:33.790 --> 30:35.240
I'll put on the costume
and run it for you.

30:35.240 --> 30:35.760
No need.

30:35.880 --> 30:36.950
We'll talk on set.

30:37.250 --> 30:38.270
I need to go find them.

30:38.270 --> 30:40.870
They change things
every day without warning.

30:41.310 --> 30:41.940
Xu.

30:42.050 --> 30:43.050
Screenwriter Xu.

30:43.830 --> 30:45.070
Screenwriter Xu.

30:45.400 --> 30:47.110
Are the musicians ready?

30:47.140 --> 30:47.720
Ready.

30:47.750 --> 30:48.880
Where's the female singer?

30:48.880 --> 30:49.280
The...

30:49.380 --> 30:49.940
I'm here.

30:53.000 --> 30:54.110
Are we singing now?

30:55.000 --> 30:55.830
No, in a bit.

30:56.900 --> 30:57.790
So beautiful.

30:57.810 --> 30:58.540
Really nice.

30:58.840 --> 30:59.640
Looking good.

31:02.750 --> 31:03.510
PA!

31:03.960 --> 31:04.640
Here.

31:05.070 --> 31:06.200
I... I'll get back to work.

31:06.200 --> 31:06.910
Go ahead.

31:08.850 --> 31:09.420
Zhuang,

31:10.040 --> 31:11.500
this outfit looks great.

31:11.550 --> 31:12.110
It's a bit hot.

31:12.110 --> 31:13.770
You really look like a singer.

31:22.790 --> 31:24.200
Thanks.

31:24.850 --> 31:25.270
Wait.

31:27.050 --> 31:28.830
This must be for Zhuang Zhuang.

31:28.980 --> 31:29.490
Here.

31:29.770 --> 31:30.230
Take it.

31:33.200 --> 31:34.030
Drink it.

31:34.610 --> 31:35.480
It's for you.

31:47.160 --> 31:48.740
What should I do? I'm still a bit nervous.

31:48.740 --> 31:49.740
Don't be nervous.

31:49.790 --> 31:50.660
With your talent,

31:50.660 --> 31:51.850
just relax.

31:53.330 --> 31:54.590
Who are we waiting for?

31:56.180 --> 31:57.130
Ranran,

31:57.240 --> 31:58.490
hurry up!

31:58.810 --> 31:59.270
Ranran.

31:59.290 --> 32:00.510
-Don’t worry.
-You're pretty enough.

32:00.510 --> 32:01.900
-We still have time.
-We won’t be late, right?

32:01.900 --> 32:02.830
Filming a movie?

32:02.880 --> 32:04.500
My place is actually quite suitable.

32:04.500 --> 32:05.070
There are many artists

32:05.070 --> 32:06.130
living at my place.

32:06.140 --> 32:07.460
They're just not very famous yet.

32:07.460 --> 32:08.010
Really?

32:08.090 --> 32:08.440
When you come to film,

32:08.440 --> 32:09.720
let them be extras.

32:09.740 --> 32:10.570
Thirty yuan a day

32:10.570 --> 32:11.770
with lunch included.

32:12.220 --> 32:13.170
That much?

32:13.500 --> 32:14.160
I heard extras

32:14.160 --> 32:15.370
only get 20 a day.

32:16.720 --> 32:17.770
Five for you, five for me.

32:17.770 --> 32:18.310
By the time they get it,

32:18.310 --> 32:19.330
it's just 20.

32:22.200 --> 32:23.930
Then regarding the venue fee,

32:24.000 --> 32:25.250
we'll follow the rules.

32:25.250 --> 32:26.310
I'll report a higher amount

32:26.310 --> 32:27.510
and you give me the kickback.

32:27.510 --> 32:28.270
I won't let you lose out.

32:28.270 --> 32:29.460
Hurry up.

32:30.140 --> 32:30.770
There are so many people.

32:30.770 --> 32:32.000
Should we split up?

32:32.030 --> 32:32.960
Let's talk when we get there.

32:32.960 --> 32:33.720
Let's go.

32:33.720 --> 32:35.050
-Talk later.
-Let’s go.

32:36.880 --> 32:38.740
These people will be famous soon.

32:38.920 --> 32:39.520
You all,

32:39.750 --> 32:40.510
perfect!

32:41.110 --> 32:42.680
This is the production manager.

32:42.680 --> 32:44.480
He's coming here to film a movie.

32:44.690 --> 32:46.450
-This is the artist I told you about.
-He’s a film producer.

32:46.450 --> 32:47.050
Look.

32:53.350 --> 32:54.010
From Henan.

32:56.180 --> 32:57.510
The one who auditioned.

32:58.750 --> 32:59.660
Xu Shengli,

32:59.830 --> 33:01.290
you are really something!

33:02.300 --> 33:02.910
Manager.

33:07.770 --> 33:08.210
Okay.

33:08.240 --> 33:09.100
Buy everything on this list.

33:09.100 --> 33:10.040
Okay, Manager.

33:16.710 --> 33:17.450
Manager.

33:17.610 --> 33:18.140
Manager.

33:18.450 --> 33:19.870
-Well, we…
-Lin.

33:20.270 --> 33:21.400
Manager, what's up?

33:22.050 --> 33:22.640
Take this,

33:22.640 --> 33:24.270
and give it to the director for me.

33:24.270 --> 33:24.770
At noon,

33:24.830 --> 33:26.500
a TV crew is coming for an interview.

33:26.500 --> 33:27.960
Make sure lunch is arranged properly.

33:27.960 --> 33:28.460
Don't worry.

33:28.460 --> 33:29.220
Here. Take these walnuts.

33:29.220 --> 33:30.290
Go scrub them for me.

33:30.290 --> 33:31.920
Scrub them for at least an hour.

33:31.920 --> 33:33.140
Don't break the tips.

33:33.530 --> 33:34.510
Okay, I will.

33:34.980 --> 33:35.650
Manager.

33:35.940 --> 33:37.230
Manager, listen to me.

33:37.350 --> 33:38.660
The director said the budget was limited,

33:38.660 --> 33:39.240
so I...

33:39.400 --> 33:40.920
Xu, Xu, Xu.

33:41.720 --> 33:43.780
I realized you're really something.

33:44.270 --> 33:44.660
Look.

33:44.720 --> 33:45.590
Even I, as the manager,

33:45.590 --> 33:47.420
don't know how to play the system
as well as you.

33:47.420 --> 33:48.090
You brought in

33:48.090 --> 33:49.330
so many of your friends and relatives.

33:49.330 --> 33:50.570
No, let me explain.

33:50.570 --> 33:51.440
No need to explain.

33:51.440 --> 33:52.220
No need to explain.

33:52.220 --> 33:54.020
I've already told the director.

33:54.380 --> 33:55.460
My place

33:55.570 --> 33:56.160
is too humble

33:56.160 --> 33:57.590
for a big star like you.

33:57.680 --> 33:58.140
Just go.

33:58.250 --> 33:58.870
Amen.

33:58.900 --> 33:59.900
Amen.

33:59.900 --> 34:00.610
-Manager.
-Just go.

34:00.610 --> 34:01.510
Amen.

34:06.490 --> 34:09.360
[Seasons Change Hostel]

34:10.290 --> 34:11.030
Mr. Xu.

34:13.520 --> 34:14.920
Did you see the director?

34:15.350 --> 34:15.949
I did.

34:17.260 --> 34:18.790
The director is quite busy.

34:18.840 --> 34:19.820
He said hello to me,

34:19.820 --> 34:21.020
and went back to work.

34:23.030 --> 34:24.130
I don't know much

34:24.130 --> 34:25.230
about your crew.

34:25.630 --> 34:26.699
But technically,

34:27.010 --> 34:27.860
we all got in

34:27.860 --> 34:28.989
through auditions.

34:29.130 --> 34:31.460
The director shouldn't blame you, right?

34:33.820 --> 34:35.699
I just joined the crew too

34:36.440 --> 34:38.770
and I was pulling strings behind his back.

34:38.960 --> 34:40.250
Although I meant well,

34:41.030 --> 34:42.550
I got busted, didn't I?

34:44.320 --> 34:45.900
My manager told me

34:45.900 --> 34:47.560
that he spoke to the director.

34:48.440 --> 34:49.800
He said that from now on,

34:50.230 --> 34:51.690
I don't have to go anymore.

34:56.340 --> 34:57.400
It's that serious?

34:58.280 --> 34:59.500
Then... then let's go together

34:59.500 --> 35:00.570
to explain to the director.

35:00.570 --> 35:01.150
How about that?

35:01.150 --> 35:01.880
No, no.

35:02.780 --> 35:03.940
That would make things worse.

35:03.940 --> 35:05.030
Really, no need.

35:06.710 --> 35:07.660
Right now, I...

35:07.860 --> 35:09.830
I can't really say how I feel.

35:10.980 --> 35:12.410
It feels like I...

35:13.190 --> 35:14.880
like I did something wrong.

35:15.360 --> 35:16.690
Like I let someone down.

35:17.510 --> 35:18.280
But I'm not clear

35:18.280 --> 35:19.400
on exactly why.

35:22.320 --> 35:22.840
It's just that,

35:22.840 --> 35:23.900
if Director Weng

35:24.050 --> 35:25.110
doesn't keep me on,

35:26.630 --> 35:27.510
I really don't know

35:27.510 --> 35:28.440
what I should do.

35:29.460 --> 35:30.840
You did it to help us.

35:32.500 --> 35:33.050
We can't let you

35:33.050 --> 35:34.110
be punished alone.

35:34.130 --> 35:34.590
Then...

35:35.820 --> 35:36.380
How about this?

35:36.380 --> 35:37.380
I'll go tell everyone,

35:37.380 --> 35:38.210
and we can figure something out together.

35:38.210 --> 35:39.170
No, don't.

35:39.630 --> 35:40.980
Don't tell them.

35:41.710 --> 35:43.570
It was supposed to be a good thing,

35:43.710 --> 35:45.280
so let's just protect that goodness.

35:45.280 --> 35:45.890
But...

35:45.920 --> 35:46.650
Besides,

35:48.860 --> 35:50.520
that won't solve the problem.

35:54.110 --> 35:54.970
How about this?

35:55.210 --> 35:55.610
In the next couple of days,

35:55.610 --> 35:57.340
I'll go see the director again.

35:57.670 --> 35:58.590
Like you said,

35:58.780 --> 35:59.980
no matter how it ends,

36:00.590 --> 36:01.210
I have to

36:01.210 --> 36:02.940
explain things clearly to him.

36:03.690 --> 36:04.110
Right.

36:07.900 --> 36:08.500
Thank you.

36:10.210 --> 36:11.210
I feel much better

36:11.880 --> 36:13.080
after letting it out.

36:14.940 --> 36:16.740
I don't feel so stifled anymore.

36:20.000 --> 36:20.670
We should be the ones

36:20.670 --> 36:21.800
apologizing to you.

36:21.800 --> 36:22.400
No need.

36:24.300 --> 36:24.840
Really.

36:29.260 --> 36:29.860
Director,

36:30.130 --> 36:31.760
these are the current issues

36:31.760 --> 36:32.780
in the directing team.

36:32.780 --> 36:34.510
Please see what should be done.

36:35.590 --> 36:36.880
Let's leave it at that for now.

36:36.880 --> 36:38.680
You guys go back to the set first.

36:38.930 --> 36:40.590
-Okay.
-Thank you, director.

36:53.090 --> 36:53.760
Come here.

36:59.010 --> 37:00.400
Sit down quickly.

37:00.400 --> 37:02.130
Standing there with your big frame,

37:02.130 --> 37:03.050
I have to look up

37:03.050 --> 37:04.300
to talk to you.

37:04.840 --> 37:05.210
Come.

37:12.360 --> 37:13.070
Xu.

37:14.150 --> 37:15.190
When I first asked you

37:15.190 --> 37:17.070
to join the crew,

37:17.400 --> 37:18.930
do you remember what I said?

37:19.280 --> 37:21.050
You said I should come
and watch carefully.

37:21.050 --> 37:21.450
Right.

37:21.730 --> 37:22.580
Watch what?

37:23.050 --> 37:24.750
Watch how everyone works.

37:25.630 --> 37:26.490
Xu.

37:26.730 --> 37:28.260
You're a smart kid.

37:28.530 --> 37:30.190
In this complicated environment,

37:30.190 --> 37:31.000
you should be able to see

37:31.000 --> 37:32.000
more than others.

37:33.090 --> 37:35.090
New interpersonal relationships,

37:35.570 --> 37:36.830
different classes,

37:37.300 --> 37:38.680
methods of trading,

37:39.030 --> 37:40.420
clashes between morals...

37:40.420 --> 37:41.020
Director,

37:41.630 --> 37:43.260
I overstepped.

37:43.630 --> 37:44.570
Sit, sit.

37:44.780 --> 37:45.310
Sit down.

37:45.650 --> 37:46.000
Sit.

37:49.840 --> 37:50.480
Ranran

37:51.170 --> 37:52.080
and Guo Zongbao

37:52.530 --> 37:53.780
both act well.

37:54.510 --> 37:55.260
And those two musicians

37:55.260 --> 37:57.230
you brought in...

37:57.340 --> 37:58.980
They really saved the day.

37:59.440 --> 38:01.060
If you were a producer

38:01.360 --> 38:02.760
or a casting director,

38:02.940 --> 38:04.940
you would have done a great service.

38:05.510 --> 38:06.630
But

38:06.880 --> 38:08.470
this crew is too chaotic

38:09.110 --> 38:10.230
and you dove headfirst

38:10.230 --> 38:11.320
into that chaos.

38:12.780 --> 38:14.280
Do you remember when

38:14.420 --> 38:16.030
what you said when you came to the studio

38:16.030 --> 38:16.760
to see me?

38:17.360 --> 38:19.300
And when you got mad
at the people in the studio,

38:19.300 --> 38:20.500
what did you say then?

38:21.650 --> 38:23.310
I said I wanted to do a good job.

38:23.320 --> 38:24.970
Do a good job at what?

38:25.030 --> 38:26.030
Writing scripts.

38:26.030 --> 38:27.290
Being a screenwriter.

38:30.530 --> 38:32.400
I'll go talk to Manager Xue.

38:33.820 --> 38:34.730
You'll be paid per day

38:34.730 --> 38:36.000
for the past few days.

38:36.080 --> 38:37.970
Your work in the crew

38:38.320 --> 38:39.040
is now over.

38:39.260 --> 38:40.300
Director,

38:40.420 --> 38:41.920
I understand what you said.

38:41.920 --> 38:42.710
I made a mistake.

38:42.710 --> 38:43.970
I know I made a mistake.

38:44.300 --> 38:45.960
Can I still

38:45.960 --> 38:47.490
work with you in the future?

38:49.480 --> 38:51.010
I'm a director.

38:51.400 --> 38:52.670
If you want to learn screenwriting,

38:52.670 --> 38:54.580
you need to find a screenwriter.

39:17.010 --> 39:18.210
Well? Did you see him?

39:20.280 --> 39:21.880
Did you explain everything?

39:23.780 --> 39:24.640
Say something.

39:25.070 --> 39:25.630
I saw him.

39:28.230 --> 39:30.010
He taught me a lesson.

39:30.880 --> 39:32.290
What do you mean by that?

39:34.440 --> 39:35.970
Can you still work with him?

39:37.880 --> 39:40.080
He won't let me work in the crew anymore.

39:40.500 --> 39:41.960
And he paid me

39:42.900 --> 39:44.160
my salary from before.

39:52.360 --> 39:52.920
I'm sorry.

39:52.920 --> 39:54.120
It's all because of us

39:54.400 --> 39:55.320
that you lost your job.

39:55.320 --> 39:56.250
I'm teasing you.

39:59.300 --> 40:01.080
I'm just kidding.

40:01.420 --> 40:02.980
Director Weng is great.

40:03.670 --> 40:04.460
About this,

40:04.460 --> 40:05.940
he indeed lectured me,

40:06.030 --> 40:07.300
but he also shared the principle

40:07.300 --> 40:09.570
about sticking to your dream.

40:09.820 --> 40:10.840
When I heard that,

40:10.960 --> 40:13.090
I felt like the Monkey King,

40:13.280 --> 40:14.460
suddenly enlightened

40:14.460 --> 40:15.590
by Patriarch Bodhi.

40:16.090 --> 40:17.550
He let me work on the crew

40:17.590 --> 40:19.340
because he wanted to observe me.

40:19.340 --> 40:20.740
He saw my strengths

40:20.920 --> 40:22.510
but also found some issues.

40:22.540 --> 40:23.990
In the end, he told me

40:24.920 --> 40:26.450
I can work in this industry.

40:26.610 --> 40:27.840
But the most important thing,

40:27.840 --> 40:29.610
the absolute most important thing,

40:29.610 --> 40:30.510
is that he's going to introduce me

40:30.510 --> 40:31.570
to an amazing screenwriter.

40:31.570 --> 40:32.070
And...

40:32.530 --> 40:34.090
He'll let me work and learn

40:34.090 --> 40:35.490
with this screenwriter.

40:35.710 --> 40:37.260
Just like your Mr. Zheng.

40:39.960 --> 40:41.290
I was so scared just now!

40:44.940 --> 40:45.460
Yesterday when you wondered

40:45.460 --> 40:47.280
if you couldn't work with
Director Weng anymore,

40:47.280 --> 40:48.300
I immediately thought about how,

40:48.300 --> 40:49.320
if Mr. Zheng stopped teaching me,

40:49.320 --> 40:51.520
then all my dreams would be for nothing.

41:00.630 --> 41:01.320
For people like us

41:01.320 --> 41:03.050
who came to Beijing on impulse,

41:03.110 --> 41:03.940
Mr. Zheng and Director Weng

41:03.940 --> 41:05.210
are like a lifeline.

41:06.900 --> 41:08.150
If you lost this lifeline

41:08.150 --> 41:08.860
because of us,

41:08.860 --> 41:11.190
we'd feel guilty
for the rest of our lives.

41:12.400 --> 41:13.330
There is no "we."

41:13.840 --> 41:14.370
Only you.

41:15.300 --> 41:16.230
You... You're nice.

41:16.230 --> 41:17.830
I can't say the same for them.

41:25.070 --> 41:26.280
You're not lying to me?

41:26.280 --> 41:26.780
No.

41:27.360 --> 41:28.780
Really, I'm not.

41:29.760 --> 41:31.730
If you still feel guilty,

41:31.730 --> 41:33.510
treat me to a soda.

41:34.610 --> 41:35.570
Why should I treat you?

41:35.570 --> 41:36.970
Because you feel guilty.

41:37.060 --> 41:38.120
My treat, my treat.

41:38.570 --> 41:39.100
My treat.

41:42.730 --> 41:44.260
How many? Ten bottles?

41:45.730 --> 41:47.230
Who is the famous screenwriter?

41:47.230 --> 41:48.590
What has he written? Have I seen any?

41:48.590 --> 41:50.160
You definitely have!

41:50.550 --> 41:52.150
He writes all the big hits.

41:52.150 --> 41:54.280
But... Director Weng won't let me say.

41:54.520 --> 41:55.880
Stop talking. Stop talking.

41:55.880 --> 41:57.190
You have to learn your lesson this time.

41:57.190 --> 41:58.250
Don't mess this up.

41:59.710 --> 42:01.690
When I no longer cling to love,

42:02.110 --> 42:04.040
when I'm no longer trapped in hate,

42:04.480 --> 42:06.660
no longer moved by others' actions

42:06.900 --> 42:08.440
to joy or sorrow,

42:08.980 --> 42:11.510
no longer hung up

42:11.570 --> 42:12.980
on illusory emotions...

42:14.010 --> 42:15.610
The tears shed upon arrival,

42:16.110 --> 42:16.960
upon departure...

42:16.960 --> 42:19.680
Upon departure, will hold no love or hate.

42:20.000 --> 42:21.400
Zhuang.

42:22.920 --> 42:24.580
When are you joining the crew?

42:24.670 --> 42:25.820
Just this week.

42:26.050 --> 42:26.970
That's so fast.

42:28.550 --> 42:29.840
Will you still rent here?

42:29.840 --> 42:30.490
Yes.

42:31.110 --> 42:32.750
This is my root in Beijing.

42:33.710 --> 42:35.140
No matter where I drift,

42:35.170 --> 42:36.340
knowing I still have a bed

42:36.340 --> 42:37.230
in Beijing

42:37.230 --> 42:38.580
puts my mind at ease.

42:43.090 --> 42:45.140
If this room suddenly goes quiet,

42:45.510 --> 42:47.570
it'll take me a while to get used to it.

42:48.170 --> 42:49.170
That doesn't sound like

42:49.170 --> 42:50.790
you'll miss me.

42:55.340 --> 42:56.140
Shen Ranran.

42:56.320 --> 42:56.980
You got a call.
